README.rst
     1â†’====================================================
     2â†’pluggy - A minimalist production ready plugin system
     3â†’====================================================
     4â†’
     5â†’|pypi| |conda-forge| |versions| |github-actions| |gitter| |black| |codecov|
     6â†’
     7â†’This is the core framework used by the `pytest`_, `tox`_, and `devpi`_ projects.
     8â†’
     9â†’Please `read the docs`_ to learn more!
    10â†’
    11â†’A definitive example
    12â†’====================
    13â†’.. code-block:: python
    14â†’
    15â†’    import pluggy
    16â†’
    17â†’    hookspec = pluggy.HookspecMarker("myproject")
    18â†’    hookimpl = pluggy.HookimplMarker("myproject")
    19â†’
    20â†’
    21â†’    class MySpec:
    22â†’        """A hook specification namespace."""
    23â†’
    24â†’        @hookspec
    25â†’        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    26â†’            """My special little hook that you can customize."""
    27â†’
    28â†’
    29â†’    class Plugin_1:
    30â†’        """A hook implementation namespace."""
    31â†’
    32â†’        @hookimpl
    33â†’        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    34â†’            print("inside Plugin_1.myhook()")
    35â†’            return arg1 + arg2
    36â†’
    37â†’
    38â†’    class Plugin_2:
    39â†’        """A 2nd hook implementation namespace."""
    40â†’
    41â†’        @hookimpl
    42â†’        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    43â†’            print("inside Plugin_2.myhook()")
    44â†’            return arg1 - arg2
    45â†’
    46â†’
    47â†’    # create a manager and add the spec
    48â†’    pm = pluggy.PluginManager("myproject")
    49â†’    pm.add_hookspecs(MySpec)
    50â†’
    51â†’    # register plugins
    52â†’    pm.register(Plugin_1())
    53â†’    pm.register(Plugin_2())
    54â†’
    55â†’    # call our ``myhook`` hook
    56â†’    results = pm.hook.myhook(arg1=1, arg2=2)
    57â†’    print(results)
    58â†’
    59â†’
    60â†’Running this directly gets us::
    61â†’
    62â†’    $ python docs/examples/toy-example.py
    63â†’    inside Plugin_2.myhook()
    64â†’    inside Plugin_1.myhook()
    65â†’    [-1, 3]
    66â†’
    67â†’
    68â†’.. badges
    69â†’
